verbose_text: When the clinical characteristics of subjects were compared between the respective genotype carriers, significant differences in HDL-C levels (A/A genotype : 1.37 +/- 0.41 mmol/L, A/G : 1.42 +/- 0.31 mmol/L, G/G : 1.20 +/- 0.30 mmol/L; F = 3.54, P = 0.03) and the prevalence of low HDL-cholesterolemia (A/A genotype : 5 subjects, 16%, A/G : 4 subjects, 9%, G/G : 10 subjects, 37%; F = 0.461, P = 0.01) were observed in the obese group.
